<div class="intro">
<div class="welcome">
Welcome to ECS, the School  of Electronics and Computer Science at the University of Southampton. ECS is one of the world's leading centres for 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050111090211/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/research/">research</a>, 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050111090211/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/about/teaching/">teaching</a>, <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050111090211/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/business/">enterprise and innovation</a> in Electronics, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science.
<div class="sig">Head of School: <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050111090211/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/people/wh">Professor Wendy Hall</a></div>
</div>
<div class="headline"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050111090211/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/669"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050111090211im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_669_img&amp;maxw=200&amp;maxh=150&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=8c0e75d239639d743d11e2298aaade9d&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="Zepler Building, Highfield Campus" border="0" width="200" height="130" class="thumbnail" /></a><h2>Headline News</h2><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050111090211/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/669">Open Access: Southampton workshops to pave the way forward</a></h3><p>Open Access to scientific and academic research publications is one of the hottest topics currently engaging academic and knowledge managers, publishers, and libraries. ECS expertise in EPrints and in establishing institutional repositories will form a major part of the agenda of two <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050111090211/http://www.eprints.org/jan2005/">free workshops</a>, being held later this month for UK university institutions planning to set up their own repositories.</p><p></p></div></div><div class='rightside'>

